The methodologies focus on spatial analysis, quantile binning, and by-item variance assessments to discern patterns in humor perception related to COVID-19's spatial and psychological impact in Italy. These figures collectively describe how humor perception varied both geographically and in relation to individual differences in coping and perceived risk during the pandemic.

